{% # CSS Variables v1.9.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.9.0 — rename scheme-role variables from `--color-<role>` → `--color-role-<role>` (background, foreground, foreground-heading, foreground-muted, primary, border, shadow, primary-button-*, secondary-button-*, input-*, placeholder, disabled-*, focus-ring, backdrop + their `-rgb` companions). Disjoint namespace from `theme_color`'s `--color-<handle>`: a theme_color entry handled `background` no longer collides with the scheme role. Gradient stop interpolation also renamed (`var(--color-role-<role>)`). Touches every consumer; see `.context/docs/specs/theme-color.md` for the contract.
  - v1.8.1 — drop the empty-output guard. `::selection`, the per-scheme rules, and the gutter `:root` always emit, so `final_content` is never blank — the guard never fires its early-skip path. Direct `{{ css_variables }}` instead.
  - v1.8.0 — emit `--gradient-<handle>` from the `gradient` metaobject (linear, scheme-adaptive: stops reference per-scheme `--color-<role>` vars so one definition re-resolves per scheme). Skips the reserved `background` handle and incomplete entries.
  - v1.7.0 — emit `--color-role-foreground-heading-rgb` for translucent heading treatments; document that button/input sub-role colors are opaque-only (add `-rgb` on demand)
  - v1.6.0 — drop the hardcoded `--color-error/success/warning` block left over from `shopify-theme-experience`. Semantic colors now flow through the normal `theme_color` metaobject loop — seed `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info` entries per `.context/docs/metaobject-definitions.md`. The hardcoded values were emitted but never consumed; now consumers that reference `var(--color-warning)` etc. resolve via the standard pipeline like every other color token.
  - v1.5.1 — drop the `.shopify-section:has([data-modifiers*="color-scheme:..."])` selector from the per-scheme rule. The `:has()` matched any descendant, so a nested override block (e.g. a media block with `color-scheme:scheme-3` inside a section using `scheme-2`) silently re-matched the outer `.shopify-section` against scheme-3, clobbering the section's tokens globally. Color tokens now live only on the modifier-bearing element (`theme-section` + override blocks); descendants inherit normally. Also aligns with `section-convention.md`'s "no typography, background, or transitions on `.shopify-section`" rule.
  - v1.5.0 — drop the `--font-heading-color` alias; consumers (currently only `core.css`'s heading-color rule) read `--color-role-foreground-heading` directly. The alias was a misnomer (it carried a color, not a font property) and split the heading color into two names. Removed the assignment line; coordinate with `core.css` to point the heading rule at the source token.
  - v1.4.1 — rename `--font-heading--color` (double dash) to `--font-heading-color` for naming consistency; coordinate with `core.css` rename
  - v1.4.0 — text_style cleanups: hoist `default_font_family` out of the loop with a `system-ui` terminal fallback (fixes invalid leading comma in `font-family` when `base_text_style` is unset); drop dead `font_fallback_family` assign; switch `line_height` storage from "% × 100" to a direct decimal; `base_text_style != null` → `!= blank`
  - v1.3.0 — rename theme-color iteration output from `--<handle>-color` to `--color-<handle>` for consistency with scheme variables (`--color-role-background`, `--color-role-primary`, etc.)
  - v1.2.1 — inline the media queries inside :root via native CSS nesting; no behavior change, cleaner output
  - v1.2.0 — replace clamp-based responsive snap with explicit `@media (width >= 48rem)` overrides for font-size and gutter; clearer intent, no stealth ramp math
  - v1.1.0 — drop `experience-section` :has selector in favor of `.shopify-section`; use `base_text_style` as the default-font-family fallback (was `settings.text_style`, which does not exist in the settings schema)
  - v1.0.0 — initial
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description Emits :root and per-scheme custom properties from design-system metaobjects and settings. Designed to be captured by the caller (see `utility--core-assets`) and piped through the inline-CSS asset loader. Returns nothing when the output would be empty.

  Depends on:
  - `theme_color` metaobject — `.system.handle` + `.hex_code.value`
  - `text_style` metaobject — many fields, see `.context/docs/design-system-metaobjects.md`
  - `typeface` metaobject (nested via `text_style.font_family`)
  - Theme settings: `color_schemes` (built-in), `base_text_style`, `mono_font`, `serif_font`, `sans_serif_font`, `mobile_gutter`, `desktop_gutter`

  @example {% render 'utility--css-variables' %}
{% enddoc %}

{% capture css_variables %}
  {% # Theme colors %}
  :root {
    {% for theme_color in metaobjects.theme_color.values %}
      --color-{{ theme_color.system.handle }}: {{ theme_color.hex_code.value }};
    {% endfor %}

    {% # Gradients — scheme-adaptive: color stops reference per-scheme role vars, so one definition re-resolves per scheme. `background` handle is reserved for the scheme background-gradient. %}
    {% for gradient in metaobjects.gradient.values %}
      {% if gradient.system.handle == 'background' or gradient.color_start.value == blank or gradient.color_end.value == blank %}
        {% continue %}
      {% endif %}
      --gradient-{{ gradient.system.handle }}: linear-gradient({{ gradient.angle.value | default: 135 }}deg, var(--color-role-{{ gradient.color_start.value }}), var(--color-role-{{ gradient.color_end.value }}));
    {% endfor %}
  }

  ::selection {
    background-color: rgba(var(--color-role-primary-rgb), 0.3);
    color: var(--color-role-foreground);
  }

  {% # Color schemes %}
  {% for scheme in settings.color_schemes -%}
    {% liquid
      assign background_brightness = scheme.settings.background | color_brightness
      if background_brightness < 64
        assign opacity_subtle = 0.15
        assign opacity_muted = 0.60
        assign opacity_border_soft = 0.25
      else
        assign opacity_subtle = 0.05
        assign opacity_muted = 0.40
        assign opacity_border_soft = 0.10
      endif
    %}

    {% if forloop.index == 1 %}
      :root,
    {% endif %}
    [data-modifiers*="color-scheme:{{ scheme.id }}"] {
      --color-role-background: {{ scheme.settings.background }};
      --color-role-background-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.background.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.background.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.background.blue }};
      --gradient-background: {% if scheme.settings.background_gradient != blank %}{{ scheme.settings.background_gradient }}{% else %}{{ scheme.settings.background }}{% endif %};

      --color-role-foreground: {{ scheme.settings.foreground }};
      --color-role-foreground-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.foreground.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.foreground.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.foreground.blue }};

      --color-role-foreground-heading: {{ scheme.settings.foreground_heading }};
      --color-role-foreground-heading-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.foreground_heading.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.foreground_heading.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.foreground_heading.blue }};
      --color-role-primary: {{ scheme.settings.primary }};
      --color-role-primary-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.primary.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.primary.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.primary.blue }};
      --color-role-border: {{ scheme.settings.border }};
      --color-role-border-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.border.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.border.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.border.blue }};
      --color-role-shadow: {{ scheme.settings.shadow }};
      --color-role-shadow-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.shadow.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.shadow.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.shadow.blue }};

      {% comment %} Button + input sub-role colors are opaque-only; add a -rgb companion here on demand for translucent treatments. {% endcomment %}
      --color-role-primary-button-bg: {{ scheme.settings.primary_button_background }};
      --color-role-primary-button-text: {{ scheme.settings.primary_button_text }};
      --color-role-primary-button-border: {{ scheme.settings.primary_button_border }};
      --color-role-secondary-button-bg: {{ scheme.settings.secondary_button_background }};
      --color-role-secondary-button-text: {{ scheme.settings.secondary_button_text }};
      --color-role-secondary-button-border: {{ scheme.settings.secondary_button_border }};

      --color-role-input-bg: {{ scheme.settings.input_background }};
      --color-role-input-text: {{ scheme.settings.input_text }};
      --color-role-input-text-rgb: {{ scheme.settings.input_text.red }}, {{ scheme.settings.input_text.green }}, {{ scheme.settings.input_text.blue }};
      --color-role-input-border: {{ scheme.settings.input_border }};

      --opacity-subtle: {{ opacity_subtle }};
      --opacity-muted: {{ opacity_muted }};
      --opacity-border-soft: {{ opacity_border_soft }};

      --color-role-primary-button-bg-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-primary-button-bg), black 12%);
      --color-role-primary-button-text-hover: var(--color-role-primary-button-text);
      --color-role-primary-button-border-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-primary-button-border), black 12%);
      --color-role-secondary-button-bg-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-secondary-button-bg), var(--color-role-foreground) 8%);
      --color-role-secondary-button-text-hover: var(--color-role-secondary-button-text);
      --color-role-secondary-button-border-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-secondary-button-border), black 12%);
      --color-role-input-bg-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-input-bg), var(--color-role-foreground) 4%);
      --color-role-input-border-hover: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-role-input-border), var(--color-role-foreground) 20%);

      --color-role-foreground-muted: rgba(var(--color-role-foreground-rgb), var(--opacity-muted));
      --color-role-placeholder: rgba(var(--color-role-input-text-rgb), 0.5);
      --color-role-disabled-bg: rgba(var(--color-role-foreground-rgb), var(--opacity-subtle));
      --color-role-disabled-text: rgba(var(--color-role-foreground-rgb), 0.4);
      --color-role-disabled-border: rgba(var(--color-role-foreground-rgb), var(--opacity-border-soft));
      --color-role-focus-ring: var(--color-role-primary);
      --color-role-backdrop: rgba(var(--color-role-shadow-rgb), 0.5);

      --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px rgba(var(--color-role-shadow-rgb), 0.06);
      --shadow-md: 0 4px 12px rgba(var(--color-role-shadow-rgb), 0.10);
      --shadow-lg: 0 8px 24px rgba(var(--color-role-shadow-rgb), 0.14);
    }
  {% endfor %}

  {% # Text styles %}
  {% liquid
    assign base_text_style = settings.base_text_style
    assign default_font_family = base_text_style.font_family.value.name.value | default: 'system-ui'
    assign hn_style_list = 'h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6' | split: ','
  %}

  {% for text_style in metaobjects.text_style.values %}
    {% liquid
      assign style_handle = text_style.system.handle

      assign font_family = text_style.font_family.value.name.value | default: default_font_family
      case text_style.font_fallback_family.value
        when 'mono'
          assign font_fallback_family = settings.mono_font

        when 'serif'
          assign font_fallback_family = settings.serif_font

        else
          assign font_fallback_family = settings.sans_serif_font
      endcase
      assign font_family = font_family | append: ', ' | append: font_fallback_family.family | append: ', ' | append: font_fallback_family.fallback_families

      assign font_style = text_style.font_style.value | default: 'normal'

      assign mobile_font_size = text_style.mobile_font_size.value | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3
      assign desktop_font_size = text_style.desktop_font_size.value | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3
      if mobile_font_size == 0 and desktop_font_size == 0
        assign mobile_font_size = 1.0
        assign desktop_font_size = 1.0
      elsif mobile_font_size == 0
        assign mobile_font_size = desktop_font_size
      elsif desktop_font_size == 0
        assign desktop_font_size = mobile_font_size
      endif

      assign line_height = text_style.line_height.value | round: 2
      if line_height == 0
        assign line_height = 1.5
      endif

      assign font_weight = text_style.weight.value | default: '400'
      assign letter_spacing = text_style.letter_spacing.value | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3

      assign text_style_transform = 'none'
      if text_style.uppercase.value == true
        assign text_style_transform = 'uppercase'
      endif

      assign text_style_decoration = 'none'
      if text_style.underline.value == true
        assign text_style_decoration = 'underline'
      endif
    %}

    :root {
      --{{ style_handle }}-font-family: {{ font_family }};
      --{{ style_handle }}-font-style: {{ font_style }};
      --{{ style_handle }}-font-size: {{ mobile_font_size }}rem;

      --{{ style_handle }}-line-height: {{ line_height }};

      --{{ style_handle }}-font-weight: {{ font_weight }};
      --{{ style_handle }}-letter-spacing: {{ letter_spacing }}rem;

      --{{ style_handle }}-text-transform: {{ text_style_transform }};
      --{{ style_handle }}-text-decoration: {{ text_style_decoration }};

      {% if base_text_style != blank and text_style == base_text_style %}
        --base-font-family: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-family);
        --base-font-style: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-style);
        --base-font-size: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-size);
        --base-line-height: var(--{{ style_handle }}-line-height);
        --base-font-weight: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-weight);
        --base-letter-spacing: var(--{{ style_handle }}-letter-spacing);
        --base-text-transform: var(--{{ style_handle }}-text-transform);
        --base-text-decoration: var(--{{ style_handle }}-text-decoration);
      {% endif %}

      {% if mobile_font_size != desktop_font_size %}
        @media (width >= 48rem) {
          --{{ style_handle }}-font-size: {{ desktop_font_size }}rem;
        }
      {% endif %}
    }

    {% if hn_style_list contains style_handle %}
      {{ style_handle }},
    {% endif %}
    [data-text-style='{{ style_handle }}'],
    [data-modifiers*='text-style:{{ style_handle }}'] {
      font-family: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-family);
      font-style: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-style);
      font-size: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-size);
      line-height: var(--{{ style_handle }}-line-height);
      font-weight: var(--{{ style_handle }}-font-weight);
      letter-spacing: var(--{{ style_handle }}-letter-spacing);
      text-transform: var(--{{ style_handle }}-text-transform);
      text-decoration: var(--{{ style_handle }}-text-decoration);
    }
  {% endfor %}

  {% # Spacing %}
  {% liquid
    assign mobile_gutter = settings.mobile_gutter | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3
    assign desktop_gutter = settings.desktop_gutter | divided_by: 16.0 | round: 3
  %}
  :root {
    --mobile-gutter: {{ mobile_gutter }}rem;
    --desktop-gutter: {{ desktop_gutter }}rem;
    --gutter: var(--mobile-gutter);

    {% if mobile_gutter != desktop_gutter %}
      @media (width >= 48rem) {
        --gutter: var(--desktop-gutter);
      }
    {% endif %}
  }
{% endcapture %}

{{ css_variables }}
